               <head>Grant of mines; 1448</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="en">English</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de la <surname>Pole</surname>, marquis and earl of <placeName role="earl" type="earldom" key="place_100076">Suffolk</placeName>
                           and of <placeName role="earl" type="earldom" key="place_105096">Pembroke</placeName></persName>, grants to
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Adrian</forename> 
                           <surname>Spierins</surname>, clerk</persName>, in consideration of
                  his work certain mines of gold and silver and other metals, all the "testewerke, dedewerke, afterwasshe and slagges" that come from the mines, for a term of 16 years without
                  any payment, and also an annuity of Â£20 until he be preferred to a stately benefice
                  of holy church fitting his degree. 
                  Dated <origDate when="1448-02-03">3 Feb., 26 Hen. VI (1448)</origDate><!--1447-09-01|1448-08-31-->. 
                  [With autograph signature.]
                  
                  </p>
